# Project Rules

## General

- Follow Spec-Driven Development (SDD).
- Never implement features without an approved spec.
- Modify only files required for the current task.
- Do not invent requirements.
- Reuse existing components before creating new ones.

## Architecture

- Respect project architecture.
- Keep business logic outside UI.
- Use dependency inversion when applicable.
- Avoid duplicate code.

## Development

- Keep changes small.
- One responsibility per file.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Follow project naming conventions.

## AI Behavior

Before generating code:

1. Read the current spec.
2. Read related architecture.
3. Read related design documentation.
4. Search for reusable code.

Never:

- Refactor unrelated code.
- Add dependencies without justification.
- Modify unrelated features.

## Git Operations

Never execute Git commands automatically.

The AI may suggest Git commands, but all Git operations must be explicitly requested by the developer.

## Output

Generate production-ready code.

Avoid placeholders unless explicitly requested.

Keep explanations concise.